<P>
   IMPEACH _ WASHINGTON _ Some advance to what's coming up this
week in impeachment investigation _ depends on actions throughout
the week. Will the House Judiciary Committee vote this week? (Carr,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   ISSUEADS _ WASHINGTON _ With the 1998 elections now over, there
is broad consensus among analysts of both parties that the
post-Watergate campaign finance system is dead. Soft money issue
ads, used aggressively by both parties in the 1998 elections, have
completely destroyed contribution limits and created a new
political environment where ``anything goes.'' Some analysts
believe there is some good news here. Unregulated third-party
advertising, the concern of the 1996 elections, has been replaced
by the parties, allowing the parties to reclaim some of their lost
influence in the political process and offering better
accountability to voters. Others such as Sen. Russ Feingold
(D-Wis.) argue that the need for reform has never been greater.
(Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
