<SLUG> BC-OBIT-CROTHERS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GEORGE CROTHERS, 89, PRODUCED CBS SHOW `LAMP UNTO MY FEET' 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Colo., Fla., Ohio)  (rl) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   George D. Crothers, a producer of the long-running CBS
television program ``Lamp Unto My Feet'' and a director of
religious broadcasting at the network, died Nov. 27 in Sarasota,
Fla. He was 89.
</P>
<P>
   ``Lamp Unto My Feet'' focused on religious and cultural issues
and was a fixture on CBS on Sunday mornings from 1948 to 1979.
</P>
<P>
   Born in Fort Morgan, Colo., Crothers graduated from Wooster
College in Wooster, Ohio, and received a doctorate in modern
European history from Columbia University. He taught at Columbia
until 1946, when he joined the Columbia Broadcasting System, where
he worked for 30 years in public affairs. Crothers was also
moderator of the radio program ``Invitation to Learning.''
</P>
<P>
   He is survived by his wife, Angelica; a son, Michael, of
Congers, N.Y.; four grandchildren; and five great-grandchildren.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
