<HEADLINE>
FANS HURT IN FALL AT STADIUM 
</HEADLINE>
  (rl) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA _ A waist-high railing gave way at Veterans Stadium
during the Army-Navy game Saturday, causing injuries to nine
spectators who fell about 15 feet to the artificial turf.
</P>
<P>
   The extent of the injuries was not known, although CBS-TV
reported that the most serious was a broken leg.
</P>
<P>
   The game was delayed for 38 minutes during the fourth quarter
while four ambulance crews attended to four students from the
Military Academy and five from its prep school at Fort Monmouth,
N.J. The names of the injured students were not released.
</P>
<P>
   The fans, who were standing between Sections 271 and 272, were
cheering for CBS cameras after Army's Ty Amey had run 70 yards for
a touchdown that put the Cadets ahead by 31-30 with 7 minutes 33
second to go in the game. The students were not being shown on
television when the accident happened, but CBS later showed it on
videotape.
</P>
</TEXT>
